08/05/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A declaration issued at the end of a two-day conference of the Balkan Political Club in Sarajevo on Sunday (7 May) called for the strengthening of BiH state institutions as key to Euro-Atlantic integration.
The signatories also pledged support for the full liberalisation of trade in the Western Balkans and called for the easing of the mutual visa regime on a reciprocal basis.
A number of former and current Balkan political leaders and prominent intellectuals spoke at the forum, addressing the international community's role in BiH and the region.
Also Sunday, BiH Foreign Minister Mladen Ivanic met with Romanian counterpart Mihai Razvan Ungureanu within the framework of the conference.
They announced the future opening of a BiH embassy in Bucharest.
(Dnevni avaz - 08/05/06;
PBS BiH, RTRS - 07/05/06)
